<h2 id="mapping">4. Axis mapping</h2>
<p>The five requested chirps map onto the quantities <code>updateSetpoint()</code> already consumes:</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th><code>CA_CHIRP_MODE</code></th><th>Chirp</th><th>Injected into</th><th>Physical effect</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>1</td><td>Cyclic pitch</td><td><code>control_sp(PITCH)</code></td><td>symmetric cyclic (both rotors)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>2</td><td>Cyclic yaw</td><td><code>control_sp(YAW)</code></td><td>differential cyclic</td></tr>
    <tr><td>3</td><td>Collective</td><td><code>collective_pitch</code> term</td><td>symmetric collective pitch</td></tr>
    <tr><td>4</td><td>Collective roll</td><td><code>control_sp(ROLL)</code></td><td>differential collective</td></tr>
    <tr><td>5</td><td>RPM</td><td>motor command (<code>actuator_sp 0/1</code>)</td><td>rotor speed sweep</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p class="small">
Rotor RPM and collective both derive from <code>THRUST_Z</code> in the stock code, so a clean RPM chirp and a clean
collective chirp are <strong>decoupled</strong>: collective is swept on the collective-pitch term while the motor is held
at <code>CA_CHIRP_RPM</code>; RPM is swept on the motor command while collective/cyclic stay at baseline.
</p>

<pre><code><span class="tok-c">// applyChirp() — bypasses the MC setpoint and routes the chirp onto one axis</span>
<span class="tok-k">void</span> ActuatorEffectivenessTwinRotorTailsitter::<span class="tok-f">applyChirp</span>(<span class="tok-k">float</span> t, matrix::Vector&lt;<span class="tok-k">float</span>, NUM_AXES&gt; &amp;sp,
        <span class="tok-k">float</span> &amp;motor_cmd, <span class="tok-k">float</span> &amp;collective_add)
{
    <span class="tok-k">const float</span> c = _chirp.<span class="tok-f">finished</span>(t) ? <span class="tok-n">0.f</span> : _chirp.<span class="tok-f">update</span>(t);

    sp.<span class="tok-f">setAll</span>(<span class="tok-n">0.f</span>);          <span class="tok-c">// bypass the MC controllers</span>
    collective_add = <span class="tok-n">0.f</span>;
    motor_cmd = _chirp_rpm;   <span class="tok-c">// hold the rotor at the configured speed</span>

    <span class="tok-k">switch</span> (_chirp_mode) {
    <span class="tok-k">case</span> CHIRP_CYCLIC_PITCH:    sp(ControlAxis::PITCH) = c; <span class="tok-k">break</span>;
    <span class="tok-k">case</span> CHIRP_CYCLIC_YAW:      sp(ControlAxis::YAW)   = c; <span class="tok-k">break</span>;
    <span class="tok-k">case</span> CHIRP_COLLECTIVE_ROLL: sp(ControlAxis::ROLL)  = c; <span class="tok-k">break</span>;
    <span class="tok-k">case</span> CHIRP_COLLECTIVE:      collective_add = c;         <span class="tok-k">break</span>;
    <span class="tok-k">case</span> CHIRP_RPM:             motor_cmd = _chirp_rpm + c; <span class="tok-k">break</span>;
    <span class="tok-k">default</span>: <span class="tok-k">break</span>;
    }
}</code></pre>

